{
  "stem": "1753.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 90.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, one of the things I neglected to mention, when-- as we went-- that we were led through the city, through that crazy mob that beat us up, we couldn't help but noticing many of the windows of the Jewish establishments and department stores being banged in and broken.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- and there were a couple of banking houses that-- that were very prominent, by the name of [?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Fidel ?] [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Humburger, ?] in-- in Karlsruhe.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they just through every imaginable piece of business machine out the window into the street.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it was a-- it was a day to remember.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But in any case, so now, the engineer, Guggenheim family, they liquidated their business.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I had some distant relatives that lived in-- in Karlsruhe.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I moved in with them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And it was impossible to-- to get a job or do anything.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So the only place you could work, as allowed by the city of Karlsruhe, was there a-- an area outside where they-- there was a big trash dump, and to do-- to straighten out the area, to reclaim land.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I worked there with a bunch of other-- oh, maybe were about 25 other young Jewish men-- until the 26th of May, 1939.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "A few days earlier, I received a-- some advice by the-- the local government, that I have to leave Germany and rejoin my family in Poland.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So on the 26th of May, 1939, I went on the train and got reunited with my family, including my father, who since already was in Poland, but came to-- to be with the rest of the family.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I was-- and arrived there a day later.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I was reunited with them on the 27th of May, 1939.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
